div.p:
Why ſhou'd we then be Laught out of Pudding and Dumpling? or why
Ridicul'd out of Good Living? Plots and Politics may hurt us, but Pudding cannot. Let us therefore adhere to Pudding, and keep our ſelves out of Harm's Way; according to the Golden Rule laid down by a celebrated Dumpling-Eater now defunct;
Be of your Patron's Mind, whate'er he ſays:
Sleep very much; Think little, and Talk leſs:
Mind neither Good nor Bad, nor Right nor Wrong;
But Eat your Pudding, Fool, and Hold your Tongue. PRIOR.
